<item>
            <title>[LU-17775] Allow &apos;lfs setstripe --copy FID&apos; to inherit layout from FID</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17775</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;It would be useful to allow &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs setstripe --copy &lt;em&gt;FID&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; (and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs mirror extend ...&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; and &quot;&lt;tt&gt;lfs migrate ...&lt;/tt&gt;&quot;) to inherit the default layout from &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;em&gt;FID&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; instead of having to specify a full pathname. This is useful for operations that are working on the source file by FID and don&apos;t know the full pathname of the parent (and don&apos;t want the overhead of doing &lt;tt&gt;fid2path&lt;/tt&gt; repeatedly).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In theory it would be possible to also use &quot;&lt;tt&gt;&lt;em&gt;MOUNT&lt;/em&gt;/.lustre/fid/FID&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; for this, but at some cost in usability.  &lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
